node.text:
.
I spent 48 hours at #PradaModeParis exploring art projects and data visualizations by AI Researcher Kate Crawford and Artist / Researcher Trevor Paglen.

The works of art showcased not only challenged my design thinking to observe beyond the surface bias-is of facial recognition and data gathering ; but to also think deeper into how such technologies could be utilized to usher in new forms of art. All while connecting people together on both an empathetic and emotional level.

@prada 
#PradaModeParis.

P.S. Thank you to my family @noor.
.
And big thanks to the Prada team
. 
@carminespena @camillachiappetta 
@santabelva 
Such a blessing.

node.text:
"why not" tells the story of what happens when we altered our reality from what is, to what could be. 
.
how we could leverage innovations in technology to properly build out our ideas and to scale our possibilities.
.
how we could be bigger than just the problems we're faced with, but also be sources of their intrinsic solutions.
.
excited for @spatial_labs to have been a part of this project in collaboration with @jumpman23 and @russwest44.
.
more experiences to follow soon.
.
directed by @tevin.jordan

streaming an iPhone via edge cloud 
with support for advanced hand tracking using only monochromatic depth camera's - AR Glasses
.
this is just a glimpse at the technologies we're building at @spatial_labs 
.
soon you won't need your phone, laptop, TV, or any vertical /horizontal 2D display for that matter.
.
you'll be able to spawn it from thin air into your environment in high precision and accuracy at 1:1 ratio.
.
game changing innovation for countries where buying physical technologies isn't affordable, they can stream the software equivalent.
.
similar to how VST'S and DAW's changed the music industry, we're going to shift the way we think of technology
.
music by @c.syresmith

Happy Black Future Month.

a close look at Canvas, a virtual interface we're creating at sLABs for our smart glasses. 👓
.
an immersive interface that's let's you stream your laptop, shop, or even view COVID cases around you in 3D.
.
all using your hands through smart glasses.
.
one of my goals is to accelerate the democratization and access to technology through cloud / spatial computing.
.
spatial reality allows us to do just this while increasing the dimensional bandwidth conveyable through technology.
.
technology starts to be interacted and used in a natural way.
.
the dimensions for what is possible as well as the tools for expanding and contracting the molecules within an infinite canvas will push the boundaries of innovation.
.
this is the future we're building at sLABS
